They were known as "The Sunshine Sisters in 1939 when they worked at radio station WLAP in Lexington, Kentucky. In 1940 they moved to Kentucky's Renfrow Valley Barn Dance to become members of Lily May Ledford;s famed Coon Creek Girls string band. The following years they moved to WSM in Atlanta, Georgia where they became known as "Mattie, Marthie and Minnie, the Hoot Owl Holler Girls." They recorded as "The Amber Sisters" for Capitol and as "Mattie, Marthie and Minnie" for King. The group disbanded due to marriages. Opal Jean formed a duo with her husband, Salty Holmes and Irene Ethel formed a duo with husband, James Roberts.
